<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1807,2013]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">
<taxonomicName box="[199,436,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunipennis">
<emphasis box="[199,436,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">Bittacus brunipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the three species of the “group 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Souza Lopes &amp; Mangabeira" authorityYear="1942" box="[936,1044,1845,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angrensis">
<emphasis box="[936,1044,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">angrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (see comments in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Souza Lopes &amp; Mangabeira" authorityYear="1942" box="[1283,1426,1845,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angrensis">
<emphasis box="[1283,1426,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">B. angrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S." box="[158,454,1879,1904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref14802" refString="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S. (2000) Three new species of Thyridates Navas, 1908 (Mecoptera, Bittacidae) from Brazil, with new combinations and some comments about phylogenetic relationships within the genus. Contribuicoes Avulsas Sobre a Historia Natural do Brasil, Serie Zoologia, 21, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2000">Collucci &amp; Amorim 2000</bibRefCitation>
). The species is known only by the female 
<typeStatus box="[936,1037,1879,1904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">holotype</typeStatus>
, which is very similar to specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Souza Lopes &amp; Mangabeira" authorityYear="1942" box="[187,332,1917,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angrensis">
<emphasis box="[187,332,1917,1940]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">B. angrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This similarity was noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S." box="[709,1037,1916,1941]" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref14802" refString="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S. (2000) Three new species of Thyridates Navas, 1908 (Mecoptera, Bittacidae) from Brazil, with new combinations and some comments about phylogenetic relationships within the genus. Contribuicoes Avulsas Sobre a Historia Natural do Brasil, Serie Zoologia, 21, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2000">Collucci &amp; Amorim (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, who mentioned the color of the pterostigma as the main character to distinguish these two species. This character however, does not seem very strong, since it shows some plasticity in other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[832,924,1989,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[832,924,1989,2012]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">Bittacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting that 
<taxonomicName box="[1127,1297,1988,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunipennis">
<emphasis box="[1127,1297,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">B. brunipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Souza Lopes &amp; Mangabeira" authorityYear="1942" box="[295,436,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angrensis">
<emphasis box="[295,436,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="307">B. angrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because the species was described from a female, the identification of 
<taxonomicName box="[1269,1436,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunipennis">
<emphasis box="[1269,1436,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="307">B. brunipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains uncertain mainly because the shape of the male epandrium is one of the most important characters to distinguish 
<taxonomicName box="[282,374,225,248]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[282,374,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="307">Bittacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. The collection of male specimens close to the type locality, Campos do Jordão State Park (
<collectingRegion box="[217,336,260,285]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="307">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
), will be needed to solve this question.
</paragraph>
